<span id="freeTextContainer18042790893307760391">I have read this story probably a dozen times and today I realized something I had missed in all those readings--they were young. Montresor and Fortunato were young men when this happened. And that has changed my entire perception of this story, making it even more horrible than it has ever been to me.<br/><br/>One of my favorite Poe stories, I find it so revealing of both men&apos;s characters. False pride and hubris drive them both. I marvel at how Poe can not only sketch a story, but also a character, in so</span>
  <span id="freeText18042790893307760391" style="display:none">I have read this story probably a dozen times and today I realized something I had missed in all those readings--they were young. Montresor and Fortunato were young men when this happened. And that has changed my entire perception of this story, making it even more horrible than it has ever been to me.<br /><br />One of my favorite Poe stories, I find it so revealing of both men's characters. False pride and hubris drive them both. I marvel at how Poe can not only sketch a story, but also a character, in so few pages.</span>
